Patch Set 4:

it seems is caused in subunit module,in v2.py,

def _parse(self, packet, result):
            ...
            remainder = self.source.read(length - 6)
            if len(remainder) != length - 6:
                raise ParseError(
                    'Short read - got %d bytes, wanted %d bytes' % (
                    len(remainder), length - 6))

I got the ParseError in my environment as:
------------------------
ParseError('Short read - got 65530 bytes, wanted 158750 bytes',)
------------------------

I have no time to dig more why this happen, may need to include some experts from subunit module

Patch Set 4:

Thanks for looking, Liang.  Glad you were able to get it to happen in your local environment, I don't think anyone else has.
